\title{OpenBCI Ultracortex Mark IV (Comfort Modifications)}
\author{monaduck1069}
\import{macros}
\date{2026-03-31}
\taxon{reference}
\tag{electrode}
\tag{comfort}
\tag{3d-print}

\p{The Ultracortex Mark IV is OpenBCI's flagship 3D-printable headset. Full 10-20 system coverage, Cyton-compatible, GPL-3.0 licensed, 373 GitHub stars. Out of the box, comfort is mediocre — the rigid PLA frame and fixed-pin electrodes create pressure hotspots during extended sessions. With modifications, it becomes a viable long-session platform.}

\subtree{
\title{Stock Design}

\ul{
  \li{3D-printed PLA shell with adjustable node positions on a geodesic frame}
  \li{Dry spiked electrodes or optional comfort (flat) electrodes}
  \li{Spring-loaded electrode holders ("Octabolts") provide some compliance}
  \li{Fits head circumferences 54-60cm via adjustable frame}
}

\p{GitHub: \code{https://github.com/OpenBCI/Ultracortex} (Mark_IV directory)}
}

\subtree{
\title{Comfort Modifications for Extended Sessions}

\ol{
  \li{\strong{Replace PLA nodes with TPU}: Reprint the electrode-holding Octabolts in TPU Shore A 85-93. The flexible material absorbs micro-shifts instead of transmitting them as point loads to the scalp.}
  \li{\strong{Swap spike electrodes for arch electrodes} ([[bci-0010]]): The Octabolt socket accepts custom electrode inserts. Print arch electrodes with matching base diameter and snap-fit.}
  \li{\strong{Add silicone padding}: Line the inner frame rails with 2mm silicone foam tape (3M 4718 or equivalent). Prevents the rigid PLA frame from digging into the forehead and occiput.}
  \li{\strong{Reduce adduction force}: The stock headset over-tightens to chase low impedance. For extended sessions, loosen until impedance is 30-50 kΩ. The Cyton's 24-bit ADC handles this fine. Pain-free contact beats gold-standard impedance.}
  \li{\strong{Add a chin strap}: Prevents the headset from shifting under its own weight during long sessions. A simple elastic band from ear to ear under the chin. Eliminates the need for overtightening.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Comfort Verdict}

\p{The Ultracortex is the \strong{most complete} open-source headset but the \strong{least comfortable} out of the box for extended sessions. The rigid geodesic frame is structurally elegant but ergonomically hostile past 30 minutes. With the modifications above (TPU nodes, arch electrodes, padding, loosened fit), it becomes usable for 60+ minute sessions. But if starting from scratch and comfort is the priority, skip the Ultracortex frame entirely — print arch electrodes ([[bci-0010]]) directly into a fabric cap.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Source}
\p{OpenBCI. "Ultracortex Mark IV." Documentation: \code{https://docs.openbci.com/AddOns/Headwear/MarkIV/}. License: GPL-3.0.}
}
